data.title: The Glass Room
data.desc:
The Glass Room is fully-equipped to cater all your needs. The internal coffee station allows for outmost comfort with the unlimited complementary coffee, tea, water and biscuits. The room can accommodate up to 10 attendees leaving plenty of room for a wide range of events.
The space has the following facilities:
•	75 inch TV
•	HDMI connection
•	White Boards
•	Flip Chart
•      Hot beverages, water and biscuits
•      internal roller shutters to make your event more private 

In addition there is also an idyllic breakout area just outside The Glass Room where you can have a great; a cosy kitchen where you are spoilt for choice in the array of breakfast cereals. You will also have access to our newly built shower rooms to freshen up!

data.title: 10 Person Meeting Room
data.desc: A light and bright 10-person boardroom. Suitable for presentations, team meetings and formal board meetings. Refreshments, Wi-Fi and full HD presentation equipment are complimentary and catering can be arranged to suit your requirements.

data.title: 4 Person Meeting Room
data.desc:
Quaint 4 person meeting room, ideal for 1 on 1 meetings or interviews, within a newly refurbished serviced office. Friendly reception team on hand for any requirements you may have to ensure the smooth running of your meeting.
Room hire includes a serving of still & sparkling water on arrival.

data.title: 6 Person Meeting Room
data.desc: 6 person meeting room in boardroom style. Spacious  and perfect for presentations, team meetings, reviews and one to ones. Full HD equipment for presentations and free Wi-Fi available throughout. A serving of tea, coffee, biscuits, still & sparkling water on arrival, additional catering is available on request.

data.title: Conference Room 2 - Private Gardens View
data.desc: Our luxury meeting room with private gardens views, located on the first floor of a historic Georgian building, is a perfect alternative to your standard business venue. Warm setting with huge windows looking out on the stunning private gardens of Russell Square, professionally equipped with HD TV with a projector, cozy chairs, High Speed WIFI, tee and coffee facilities, specially designed for workshops, boardroom meetings, conferences or training sessions. The meeting room (550 sq. feet) can be extended by additional 550 square feet, which is a subject to arrangement and additional charge.

data.title: Sky Room
data.desc: The Sky Room is set up with the very best facilities and perfect for a group of up to 5. Your meeting is in good hands with our support team who will be on site to meet and greet your guests and prepare refreshments. Book today to secure your preferred date and time.

data.title: Meeting Room 6
data.desc: A 175sqft meeting room perfect for boardroom meetings or small workshops.

data.title: Cutty Sark
data.desc: The meeting room Cutty Sark is 3.52 Metres wide & 5.76 Metres long with a height of 2.07 Metres. The room can take up to 8 delegates Board room. It has natural daylight, air-conditioning and a beautiful view over the River Thames. All of our meeting rooms have a dedicated event host accommodating all of your event requirements. The Tower hotel offers complimentary WI-FI, pens, pads & sweets on the table as well as projector and flipchart. We can arrange tea, coffee and snacks as well as lunch if requested.

data.title: Arundal
data.desc:
Located on the Greenwich Peninsula adjacent to the 02 Arena, the Arundel is a naturally lit room that can host up to 14 people in a boardroom configuration. This room can provide plasma screens, projectors, and notepads. And upon request, we can also serve lunch and refreshments with a minuscule fee.

Location: 200 m from North Greenwich Underground Station

Perfect for meetings and interviews as well as one to one training. Work in a relaxing atmosphere with a Flat screen TV equipped, making it ideal for presentations.

data.title: Boardroom
data.desc:
Our boardroom is the ideal setting for important meetings for up to 12 people. Located within our premium flexible work space, minutes from Barbican and Old Street.

Leading design fixtures and features and state-of-the-art technology enable your meetings to go global, without leaving the comfort of your space.

The Boardroom includes audio conferencing facilities with touch-screen controls, 65” Smart TV, wired and wireless connection to screen, USB rapid charging, super-fast Ethernet and Wi-Fi, AC and heating, Concierge service, and complimentary coffee and refreshments.

In addition, Room Service is available from our onsite restaurant Palatino at extra cost, with delicious Italian working lunches created by chef Stevie Parle. (http://palatino.london/menu/)

Benefitting from high quality service, our Boardroom is the perfect space for formal meetings, international business, high profile presentations and important interviews.

https://www.foraspace.com/

data.title: Study Studio
data.desc:
The Study Studio is a bright and inspirational space, adorned with a mural by award-winning
poet Lemn Sissay. Natural daylight floods through the large windows looking out onto
picturesque and leafy Brunswick Square.

Please note: The Study Studio walls are adorned with artistic installation 'Superman was a Foundling' by contemporary artist and poet Lemn Sissay. Therefore, no posters, post it notes, or materials of any kind are to be stuck to the wall. 

The Studio comes supplied with in-house AV equipment plus free WIFI internet access. This
multi-purpose space can be set up to suit individual requirements, seating up to 50 theatre style.
